&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;OYPEnA font-feature-liga-off font-feature-clig-off font-feature-calt-off text-decoration-none text-strikethrough-none&quot;&gt;Aquatic was founded with a shared passion for tackling some of the most complex challenges in one of the world’s most competitive arenas—global financial markets. From the very beginning, we have been driven by a deep commitment to applying cutting-edge scientific research and technological innovation to deliver unparalleled performance. Our journey is one of continuous growth and exploration, marked by a spirit of curiosity and relentless drive for excellence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring an Research Business Manager to serve as the operational and strategic core of Aquatic’s research organization. This is a unique role that is responsible for ensuring that the R&amp;amp;D function operates with clarity, momentum, and purpose.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the day-to-day operating rhythm of the research team: driving project delivery, managing cross-functional dependencies, and representing the research organization to the rest of the firm. You will work directly alongside researchers, engineers, and senior leadership to translate strategy into execution and to make sure the highest-impact work is always moving forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not a coordinator role. We are looking for someone who develops genuine domain expertise, holds people accountable, and over time becomes the operational authority the research team turns to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Project Management &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the operating rhythm of the R&amp;amp;D organization: progress tracking, research progress reviews, cross-team dependency management, and milestone accountability across the full research stack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the connective tissue between research leads, engineering, and infrastructure, ensuring blockers are surfaced, escalated, and resolved rather than sitting unaddressed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive delivery of high-priority research initiatives end-to-end, from coordinating rollouts (e.g., new tooling, data pipelines, deployment phases) to tracking outcomes against business goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain clear visibility into what every team is working on, where things stand, and what is at risk and communicate this proactively to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor Management &amp;amp; Data Sourcing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with external data vendors and research tool providers: lead due diligence, evaluate offerings against research needs, coordinate with internal stakeholders, and drive contracting and onboarding.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership Materials&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare materials for internal leadership reviews: synthesize research initiatives, translate technical work into clear business narratives, and develop compelling presentations that communicate Aquatic’s research strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Operations &amp;amp; Domain Expertise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize the initiatives most likely to produce the greatest improvement to PnL; push back on work that doesn’t move the needle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and drive process improvements across the research lifecycle: from how the team tracks progress to how results are evaluated and monetized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Think strategically about Aquatic’s revenue model and how research investments connect to business outcomes; bring that lens to every prioritization conversation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
